<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be loaded • be loaded for bear</xh5><p> <i>be loaded</i>—(U.S. sl.) 1. be under the influence of drugs or alcohol: <u>I’m not loaded</u>. I’m just a little tipsy. 2. be very rich: Mr. Wilson <u>is loaded</u>, but he is also generous with his money.</p><p> <i>be loaded for bear</i>—(U.S. sl.) 1. <i>= be loaded 1: </i>Marines are always <u>loaded for bear</u>, and get nicked once in a while. 2. ready for the hardest problems: <u>I’m loaded for bear</u>, and that’s good because this is going to be a rough day. 3. very angry: By the time he finished talking, I <u>was loaded for bear</u>.</p> </entry>
